The '''''Rebellion Era Sourcebook''''' is a supplement to the ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]'', published by [[Wizards of the Coast]]. It was written by [[Bill Slavicsek]], [[Steve Miller]], and [[Owen K.C. Stephens]]. It was first published in [[2001]].

The book details material from the era of the [[original trilogy]] of films and key contemporary [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] information. It includes characters, adventure hooks, and advice on conducting a [[Rebellion era]] campaign.

==Publisher's summary==
No epic adventure has fed the imagination of millions of fans worldwide quite like the Star Wars series has. Now there's even more great information to digest. Everything that a player needs to know about the Empire and Rebel Alliance from the classic Star Wars universe can be found in this one sourcebook -- from weapon and ship statistics to information on non-player characters. Han Solo, the Death Stars, TIE interceptors, Princess Leia, stormtroopers, Luke Skywalker . . . it's all here in detail. This book will be a must-have for all Star Wars gamemasters. 

==Contents==
Comprising 159 pages, this book packs a good deal of information about the era of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Information for roleplaying is included side-by-side with a storyline during the time of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|Episodes IV]], [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|V]], and [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|VI]].

